        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/divesh/{size}/50454_2.png",
        "created_at": "2025-01-25T20:21:38.426Z",
        "cooked": "<details>\n<summary>\nCollapsed by moderator</summary>\n<blockquote>\n<p>This item already has <a href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/t/screenshot-recording-detection-and-or-blocking/46922\">an existing discussion topic</a>. Please continue any discussion there.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><strong>1. Disable Screenshots for Disappearing Messages</strong><br>\nPrevent screenshots in disappearing messages to ensure greater confidentiality and align with their purpose of safeguarding sensitive content from being captured or shared.</p>\n</details>\n<p><strong>2. Separate Chat Threads for Disappearing Messages</strong><br>\nAllow users to create separate chat threads specifically for disappearing messages, where each thread can have a custom disappearing timer set by the user. Similar to Telegram‚Äôs secret chats, these threads would be distinct from regular chats (e.g., showing abbreviated disappearing lengths like ‚Äú1w‚Äù for 1 week in the corner of the icon) and could be deleted by any participant from all devices after use. This feature would allow multiple conversations with the same contact, each with varying privacy levels.</p>\n<p>Example:<br>\na) A standard chat for regular conversations.<br>\nb) A private chat with a 1-day disappearing timer for sensitive discussions.<br>\nc) A work-related chat with a 4-week disappearing timer for temporary projects.</p>\n<p>This flexibility ensures users can manage privacy requirements for different conversations and makes it easier to integrate features like disabling screenshots seamlessly.</p>",
