        "created_at": "2025-01-25T22:21:07.575Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I do like the idea to mark disappearing chats in a special way to better distinguish them from others. But do keep in mind that the disappearing timer can be changed or switched off at will, so keeping them in a separate place could be confusing, because they would  switch back and forth  between regular and disappearing chats.</p>\n<p>Also, something you should keep in mind: Disappearing chats are not meant for protecting sensitive information. At least not more than regular chats are: <a href=\"https://support.signal.org/hc/en-us/articles/360007320771-Set-and-manage-disappearing-messages\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">https://support.signal.org/hc/en-us/articles/360007320771-Set-and-manage-disappearing-messages</a></p>",
