        "created_at": "2025-01-26T01:08:42.221Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"divesh\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"66364\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/divesh/48/50454_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> divesh:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Allow users to create separate chat threads specifically for disappearing messages, where each thread can have a custom disappearing timer set by the user. Similar to Telegram‚Äôs secret chats, these threads would be distinct from regular chats (e.g., showing abbreviated disappearing lengths like ‚Äú1w‚Äù for 1 week in the corner of the icon) and could be deleted by any participant from all devices after use. This feature would allow multiple conversations with the same contact, each with varying privacy levels.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>This is already possible with group chats. You can create any number of group chats that are just between you and the other person and set varying levels of disappearing message timers in each chat.</p>",
